Joshua Shongwane was waiting for his case to be called when he overpowered police and fatally shot one. JOHANNESBURG - The Hawks have re-arrested a man who s been on the run after the murder of an officer at the Tembisa Magistrates Court.Joshua Shongwane had been out on bail for another murder but was re-arrested earlier this year for armed robbery.While waiting for his case to be called, he overpowered police and fatally shot the officer before escaping.Shongwane was nabbed at a hideout spot in Eesterus east of Pretoria yesterday afternoon. The Hawks' Robert Netshiunda said, We ve arrested a suspect who s been wanted for killing a police officer at court in Tembisa. The man, commonly known as Bomba, was re-arrested yesterday just outside Pretoria. 